{"id": "UgyRlwK_f3Ay9Y0uYnV4AaABAg", "videoId": "LEjhY15eCx0", "authorDisplayName": "@moon_60726", "publishedAt": "2024-06-17T11:31:12Z", "likeCount": 16, "textDisplay": "I literally just came out the theatre after watching the movie and it was so good I had to write this  immediately.This movie is an absolute masterpiece! The way they portrayed everything so perfectly it was so clever and relatable at the same time!! (Spoiler alert) I absolutely LOVE how they portrayed brainstorming ideas as an ACTUAL storm of ideas and how anxiety suppressing the other emotions and how she literally froze when Riley was having a panic attack, I mean that was absolutely genius. I am about to be an adult now and in my initial teen years, this was EXACTLY how I felt, the anxiety, embarrassment, envy, sarcasm, stress, confusion, boredom, EVERYTHING ALL AT ONCE. I am still dealing with anxiety and other mental health issues and I have to say this movie definitely portrays what we as human don't know how to say. Would definitely recommend to watch this one, another masterpiece by Pixar", "parentId": null}
